msgstr "<manvolnum>1</manvolnum>"

#. Tag: refpurpose
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:18
#, no-c-format
msgid "fool <command>make</command> into not rebuilding certain files"
msgstr ""
"Dupe <command>make</command> afin de ne pas reconstruire certains fichiers"

#. Tag: cmdsynopsis
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:22
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>cheatmake</command> <group><option>hidechange</option> "
"<replaceable>file</replaceable></group> <group><option>show</option></group> "
"<group><option>why</option> <replaceable>file</replaceable></group>"
msgstr ""
"<command>cheatmake</command> <group><option>hidechange</option> "
"<replaceable>fichier</replaceable></group> <group><option>show</option></"
"group> <group><option>why</option> <replaceable>fichier</replaceable></group>"

#. Tag: title
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid "Description"
msgstr "Description"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:34
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>cheatmake</command> is used to save time when recompiling. It can "
"fool make into skipping files that haven't changed in a meaningful way. This "
"can be used for instance when you change a comment in a file but none of the "
"actual code."
msgstr ""
"<command>cheatmake</command> est utilisé pour gagner du temps lors des "
"recompilations. Il peut duper make afin d'ignorer les fichiers qui n'ont pas "
"changé de manière significative. Ceci peut être utilisé par exemple lorsque "
"vous changez un commentaire dans un fichier, sans en avoir modifié le code."

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:39
#, no-c-format
msgid "This utility is part of the &kde; Software Development Kit."
msgstr ""
"Cet utilitaire fait partie du kit de développement de logiciels de &kde;."

#. Tag: title
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:44
#, no-c-format
msgid "Options"
msgstr "Options"

#. Tag: term
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:48
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>hidechange</option> <replaceable>file</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>hidechange</option> <replaceable>fichier</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Hides the fact that file was changed by setting the timestamp into the past. "
"Use with care!"
msgstr ""
"Masque le fait que ce fichier a changé en plaçant l'horodatage dans le "
"passé. À utiliser avec précaution ! "

#. Tag: option
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:53
#, no-c-format
msgid "show"
msgstr "show"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:54
#, no-c-format
msgid "Lists what files <command>make</command> currently needs to rebuild"
msgstr "Liste les fichiers que <command>make</command> doit reconstruire"

#. Tag: term
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>why</option> <replaceable>file</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>why</option> <replaceable>fichier</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:58
#, no-c-format
msgid "Explains why make must rebuild file"
msgstr "Explique pourquoi make doit reconstruire le fichier"

#. Tag: title
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:64
#, no-c-format
msgid "Environment"
msgstr "Environnement"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:66
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"One of the following variables (but not both) should be set if the source "
"directory is different from the build directory. If the build directory is "
"simply a subdirectory of the source directory, the simpler variable "
"<envar>OBJ_SUBDIR</envar> should be used."
msgstr ""
"Une des variables suivantes (mais pas les deux) doit être réglée si le "
"dossier des sources est différent du dossier de construction. Si le dossier "
"de construction est simplement un sous-dossier du dossier contenant les "
"sources, la simple variable <envar>OBJ_SUBDIR</envar> doit être utilisée."

#. Tag: envar
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:73
#, no-c-format
msgid "OBJ_SUBJDIR"
msgstr "OBJ_SUBJDIR"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:74
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Indicates that the build directory is in the given subdirectory of the "
"source directory. For instance, if the source directory is <filename class="
"\"directory\">kdesdk</filename> and the build directory is <filename class="
"\"directory\">kdesdk/obj-i386-linux</filename>, then <envar>OBJ_SUBDIR</"
"envar> should be set to <parameter>obj-i386-linux</parameter>."
msgstr ""
"Indique que le dossier de construction est dans le sous-dossier donné du "
"dossier contenant les sources. Par exemple, si le dossier de sources est "
"<filename class=\"directory\">kdesdk</filename> et que le dossier de "
"construction est <filename class=\"directory\">kdesdk/obj-i386-linux</"
"filename>, alors <envar>OBJ_SUBDIR</envar> doit être mise à <parameter>obj-"
"i386-linux</parameter>."

#. Tag: envar
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid "OBJ_REPLACEMENT"
msgstr "OBJ_REPLACEMENT"

#. Tag: para
#: man-cheatmake.1.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A <command>sed</command> expression that is used to transform the source "
"directory into the build directory. For instance, if the source directory is "
"<filename class=\"directory\">kdesdk/obj-i386-linux</filename>, then "
"<envar>OBJ_REPLACEMENT</envar> should be set to <parameter>s#kdesdk#kdesdk-"
"obj#</parameter>."
msgstr ""
"Une expression <command>sed</command> qui est utilisée pour transformer le "
"dossier des sources en dossier de construction. Par exemple, si le dossier "
"des sources est <filename class=\"directory\">kdesdk/obj-i386-linux</"
"filename>, alors <envar>OBJ_REPLACEMENT</envar> devrait être réglée à "
"<parameter>s#kdesdk#kdesdk-obj#</parameter>."

